-- 
Ukraine Seeks Alternative to Pension Reform, Izvestia Reports

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-04-14T07:11:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/ukraine-seeks-alternative-to-pension-reform-izvestia-reports.html
Ukraine will propose to the
 International Monetary Fund  that pension reform be replaced by
other measures to cut state spending,  Ekonomicheskie Izvestia 
reported, without citing anyone.  The cabinet wants to balance the budget by raising rent for
natural deposit extraction and by cutting expenditure by
Ukravtodor, the state-run road company, the newspaper said.  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  